20/02/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Seven European prime ministers arrived in Athens on Thursday (19 February) to participate in a two-day meeting of the European People's Party (EPP). The focus is on issues related to the European Constitution and the European Parliament elections, scheduled for June. EPP Vice President and Greek opposition New Democracy (ND) Party President Costas Karamanlis expressed the conviction that ND would win the 7 March elections, strengthening the EPP majority presence in Europe. The meeting was organised by his party; guests included the prime ministers from Spain, Italy, the Netherlands, Portugal, Luxembourg, Slovakia, and Malta. (MPA, ANA - 19/02/04)
